#Ninja Gaiden II: The Dark Sword of Chaos
#HDNES/Mesen HD Pack by RichterSnipes
#Initial Release: 2017 April 20

#Note that the number following these is the fade level:

#fade = stages
#scene = cutscenes (referred to as "Tecmo Theater")
#actscreen = act screen
#opening = opening cinematic
#green = green bricks in Act I interlude (plays just after Stage 1-2)
#char = cutscenes that involve a sprite graphic of either Irene or Robert
#jaquio = Jaquio close-up used in cutscenes
#crumble = demon castle destruction cinematic (plays at the end of the game)
#end = ending cinemtaic (plays just before the credits)
#splash = 1st splash screen ("TECMO PRESENTS")
#opRyu = opening slide for Ryu (used to differentiate tile fades for opening slides)
#Robert = profile view of Robert
#actIIIint = Act III interlude (plays just after Stage 3-3)
#actIIIpre = Act III prelude (plays just before Stage 3-1)
#tower = Tower of Lahja cinematic (plays just before Stage 3-1, immediately after Act III prelude)
#castle = demon castle cinematic (plays just after Stage 6-1)
#shoot = gunshot sprite effect when Robert fires his pistol
#palace = cutscenes at Ashtar's palace (needed for shared tiles)

#xx = file I haven't gotten to yet
#bg = background, in case the target tile isn't in any files
#fx = fade x, where x is the fade level
#gx = glow x, where x is the glow cycle
#a = alternate

#A small number of cutscenes don't work with background color tiles from the HD pack. They've been deleted.
#Custom palettes can be used to change these background colors to their SNES counterparts.
#Obvious dithering has been exchanged in favor of additional shades of color.

#Most cycling palettes weren't added to the SNES version of the game, likely due to lack of time or laziness.
#They will all be used in this pack in one way or another.

#NOTE: Don't use the SNES version of the HUD. The default NGII HUD is more detailed.
#Adding the needed files would add a ton of extra files, as well.

##CHR $0000 (00_00.png)
